instructors.bio: Chelsea has traveled a unique path to bring her expression of yoga to both the tenured yogi and those who never believed the practice was for them. Chelsea received her Ph.D. in Educational Studies, making it her life's work to study the positive impact that yoga has on communities. Chelsea believes that practicing yoga connects you more deeply to yourself and the world around you, making you happier and healthier in your daily life. Chelsea's teaching style is creative, challenging and compassionate, making you feel at home with her as you build strength and confidence.
instructors.short_bio: Chelsea believes that practicing yoga connects you more deeply to yourself and the world around you. Her teaching style is creative, challenging and compassionate, making you feel at home with her while you build confidence and strength.
instructors.background: My intention is to create an environment that leaves Members with a strong sense of belonging and accomplishment. I am inspired by how yoga, music and soulful storytelling can take us on a journey closer to ourselves.
ordered_q_and_as: How Do You Motivate?

I empower you to embrace the body you are in! Yoga is an opportunity to pour love back into yourself, and can travel with you off the mat and into your life in the form of strength, peace, presence and wisdom.
Outside of Peloton

As a Ph.D. and former school teacher, I bring yoga and education to others. I created a tuition-free space for teen girls to read, write poetry, practice yoga and build a community called Yoga, Literature & Art Camp.
instructors.quote: I want to be someone people relate to. I’ll encourage you as I push you.
instructors.name: Chelsea Jackson Roberts

instructors.bio: If there’s one thing that really motivates former boxing instructor Bradley, it’s having the odds stacked against him. The moment someone says he can’t do something, well, that’s all he needs to hear to go out and do it! It’s why he’s often been labelled a rebel as he always manages to find a way to overcome life’s obstacles by doing things his way. After a decade in New York, Bradley is now back in the UK to bring his unique blend of British charm and eternally optimistic attitude to the London cycling studio. He’s a big believer that life is an adventure we shouldn’t take too seriously, so expect him to keep you smiling through his sweat-drenched sessions on the Bike.
instructors.short_bio: Boxing fan Bradley believes you’re never beaten, however big the challenge. It’s this approach to life combined with his infectious smile and a love of putting fun at the heart of his classes that will keep you coming back.
instructors.background: I want Members to leave my classes with a smile on their face KNOWING they’ve got the beating of whatever challenges they may be facing. However much of an underdog you may feel, there is always a way over that hill.
ordered_q_and_as: How Do You Motivate?

FUN is important to me! It becomes really hard to stick to something if you're not enjoying yourself, so I’ll push past whatever excuses you've got, but because you're being equally entertained, you'll hardly notice.
Outside of Peloton

I'm a keen traveller, animal lover and meditator. I've been called a rebel because I love proving people wrong, so you’re welcome to challenge me, but beware, I won't just beat you, I'll also post about it on Instagram!
instructors.quote: Sometimes you have to fight more than once to win it
instructors.name: Bradley Rose

instructors.bio: Selena is a unique combination of an Italian upbringing and a Hawaiian state of mind. Raised in Italy in a family of professional soccer players, sports were a way of life. When she moved to Hawaii for college, she developed a passion for surfing and for the spiritual side of fitness. Relocating to NYC, she channeled this into a career training as an amateur boxer and teaching boxing. Selena brings an empowering energy to Peloton, teaching Members how to tap into themselves to unleash their power, and accomplish goals they never thought they could achieve.
instructors.background: I believe we’re all capable of great things and that we all have that fire burning inside us. I want to share the things that have helped me access that fire, and that’s exactly what I get to do on the Peloton Tread!
ordered_q_and_as: How Do You Motivate?

I want Members to know that I’ve got their back, always. Every day we can push ourselves to new standards, get a little stronger, run a little faster, have a little more heart and show a little more power.
Outside of Peloton
Outside of Peloton you can find me on a surfboard or in boxing gloves. There is nothing quite like the feeling of being in perfect harmony with mother nature.
instructors.quote: DREAM IT. BELIEVE IT. RECEIVE IT.
instructors.name: Selena Samuela

instructors.bio: Born and raised in New York, Olivia grew up playing and excelling at team sports, including lacrosse, field hockey, cheerleading and track. With a professional background in finance, as well as boxing and cycling, she brings a we-first, cheerleader approach to every class, inspiring you to leave each workout walking taller and feeling stronger.
instructors.short_bio: “Decide what you want to accomplish, and I will help you conquer it.”
instructors.background: We’re gonna work, and we’re gonna work hard. Know that I’m in this with you every step of the way. I’m a natural cheerleader, and when we workout together, we’re a team. I will always have your back, no matter how challenging things get!
ordered_q_and_as: How Do You Motivate?

I like to lead by example. By staying with you throughout class, I can show you that sometimes, all it takes is getting out of your own way to accomplish your goals. You’re going to love the way you feel when we’re done!
Outside of Peloton
My first word was doggy, so you can imagine what my favorite animal is! I also love fashion, family, skincare, being outdoors, and being a crazy plant lady.
instructors.quote: “Decide what you want to accomplish, and I will help you conquer it.”
instructors.name: Olivia Amato

instructors.bio:
Rad was born and raised in the Bronx, NY in a vibrant Dominican household. Soft-spoken but resilient, he found his confidence through sports and competition. Years of hard work as a boxer led him into fitness and training. 

Physical and mental strength are key in Rad’s classes, and he’ll lead you through each workout with a little tough love. His goal is to inspire others to make them feel more confident about themselves.
instructors.background: It's a beautiful thing to be able to inspire others in a way that's going to make them feel more confident about themselves. To help someone better themselves both physically and mentally is a blessing.
ordered_q_and_as: How do you motivate?

I help you build a bigger sense of confidence. I’ll push you to find that determination within yourself, and get rid of any excuses. I make sure we have fun too, with a few dance moves and a great playlist.
Outside of Peloton?

I’m always trying to learn new things—whether a new instrument or how to make a new dish for dinner. I’m a huge fan of my city, so I like finding new places to eat. I’m big on spending time with friends and family too.
instructors.name: Rad Lopez

instructors.bio: Jess has been an athlete and leader her whole life. As a 3-year captain of her college basketball team, she motivated others through her own actions, leading her to amazing places off the court. Jess began her professional career as a school teacher who fearlessly opened new schools in underserved neighborhoods in Boston and NYC. After years in academics, Jess realized she was missing her athletic roots, and decided to leave school teaching to go back to the subject she’s most passionate about: fitness.
instructors.short_bio: “You don’t have to, you get to.”
instructors.background: I want everyone to feel like an athlete while working out, so I coach in the mindset of being in a game. I love mental breakthroughs because when we get out of our own way, out of our own head, that’s where magic happens.
ordered_q_and_as: How Do You Motivate?
Some say my style of teaching incorporates a little bit of “tough love.” I expect a lot, but I also support a lot. Remember what you want most, and forget about what you want now.
Outside of Peloton
Outside the studio, I love boxing, lifting, going to new coffee shops in the city and spending time with my three pitbulls! I am also super excited to start training for some road races in 2019.
instructors.quote: You don’t have to, you get to.
instructors.name: Jess Sims

instructors.bio: Raised in Florida, schooled in Tennessee, steeped in southern California and heat-tested in Texas, Denis brings 14 years of fitness leadership to Peloton. With an athletic history ranging from college football to aerial acrobatics, and a musical taste to match, Denis will keep you moving, grooving and guessing what comes next.
instructors.short_bio: “Learn to love the skin you’re in.”
instructors.music_bio: Check out a sample of Denis’ current class playlist.
instructors.background: This bike gives us an opportunity to reclaim our natural athleticism, even if only for a few minutes each day, which leads naturally to a renewed self image and that feeling of athleticism that had long been lying dormant.
ordered_q_and_as: How Do You Motivate?

I use music and personal stories to connect deeply between the workout, the people in the room and the Members around the world. I want to inspire people to explore their own abilities with my guidance and experience.
Outside of Peloton
I surf, practice yoga, snowboard, skateboard, hike, play guitar, read historical nonfiction, lift weights, watch college football (FSU) and look for chances to stamp my passport.
instructors.quote: Learn to love the skin you’re in
instructors.name: Denis Morton

instructors.bio: I’m a first-generation college student, and I’m proud to have broken multiple glass ceilings: I’m a black woman who has won rowing championships, I hold an advanced degree, and I’m a published author. I also run my own rowing academy! I like to keep busy.
instructors.short_bio: Ash’s classes are always a party—but when the red lipstick comes out, you’re in for a serious sweat. She’s a Big Ten champion, a seasoned coach, and she instills positivity into every stroke. With Ash, you’ll always leave feeling brighter.
ordered_q_and_as: How do you motivate?

I’m excited to bring a party on a rower. We can be weird and goofy and get an amazing workout. If you're gonna sparkle, then sparkle! I’ll challenge you to bust through the glass ceiling, and kick your butt with a smile.
Outside of Peloton

I'm learning to play the ukulele right now. It is red and her name is Ruby. And I love documentaries. Family and community are important to me—I love spending time with my loved ones, and being a cool auntie!
instructors.quote: “I’m a bull—so when we see red, we boogie!”
instructors.name: Ash Pryor

instructors.bio: Hailing from Tampico, Mexico, Mariana grew up in a family full of athletes who drew on each other’s hard work and discipline to succeed. But as she grew older, her passion for teaching became evident as she loved helping others find their inner strength. A yoga teacher for over 11 years, Mariana has taught bilingual classes from Mexico City to NYC. Her classes are a mix of warmth, tough love and infectious energy. Her goal is to make you both smile and sweat.
instructors.short_bio: Hailing from Tampico, Mexico, Mariana will draw you to her empowering light with Spanish and English classes. With a competitive athletic background, movement, breath, energy and compassion are a huge part of Mariana’s practice.
instructors.background: I love when someone who is maybe a bit resistant to yoga takes class and feels they got as much of a workout as they did during a run, Bike ride, floor class.
ordered_q_and_as: How do you motivate?
I try to approach with an open heart, open mind and shining heart.
Outside of Peloton?
Outside of Peloton, you can catch Mariana waiting in line to see the latest play or running and reading in Central Park.
instructors.name: Mariana Fernández

instructors.bio:
Callie radiates sunshine. She comes from a large family of athletes, but broke the mold to pursue dance. Years of rigorous ballet training taught her discipline, grace and strength. Her knowledge of technique and emphasis on quality of movement extends to her classes. 

Callie’s workouts are tough, but she’ll make you feel good after every class.
instructors.background: Everyone is welcome in my class. I want you to feel comfortable and confident after we work out together.
ordered_q_and_as: How do you motivate?

We can accomplish anything we put our mind to by instilling confidence. Show up as yourself, and I’ll guide you the rest of the way. Expect to work hard, laugh a little and leave with an undeniable sense of self worth.
Outside of Peloton?
When I’m not at Peloton, you can find me shopping in the pillow aisle or throwing punches in the gym. Nothing makes me happier than spending time with loved ones in the comfort of my own home.
instructors.quote: “Believe in yourself, and you're halfway there.”
instructors.name: Callie Gullickson

instructors.bio: Sam is a pro at many things but shines when it comes to motivating Members to reach their best. From the ring to the dance floor, theatre to the music room, he’s spent his life studying his two passions: fitness and the arts. After 20 years in entertainment and 15 years in fitness, Sam is ready to challenge you to go further with a perfect balance of showmanship and hustle. Sam is based in the UK and teaches live rides from our London studio.
instructors.background: I’m a student of many different disciplines, as I know we all learn and absorb in different ways. Expect a mix of technical training, showmanship and a dash of serenity to help push you.
ordered_q_and_as: How do you motivate?
I encourage Members to remember, “Why am I here?” That motivation is the element that gets us started, keeps us going and makes us want to come back for more.
Outside of Peloton
I’m a huge film, theatre and comic buff! So you will definitely catch me at a musical, at the movies or on the couch catching up with a drama or comedy series.
instructors.name: Sam Yo

instructors.bio: Hannah grew up in Portland, Oregon and came to New York City to dance. She is passionate about guiding others’ fitness journeys and watching them evolve. A kick-your-butt drill sergeant, fiery New York dancer and a West Coast flower child all at once, Hannah is dedicated to a teaching style that empowers people to appreciate how strong they are, and how to protect that strength with stretching when they hop off the Bike and head out into the world.
instructors.short_bio: "You are a rockstar. Treat yourself accordingly."
instructors.music_bio: Check out a sample of Hannah’s current class playlist.
instructors.background: Wanna hear a joke? Thinking you have limits. I teach for that moment when you realize what I've known from the start: you can do this, and you're stronger than you know.
ordered_q_and_as: How Do You Motivate?
Treat your body like it belongs to someone you love. Admire your strength, and take time to recover. And always ask yourself, #didyoustretchtho?
Outside of Peloton
I'm on a quest to hang upside down from every ceiling on silks, hug every tree in the Northeast, and dance down every street in Manhattan.
instructors.quote: You are a rockstar. Treat yourself accordingly.
instructors.name: Hannah Corbin

instructors.bio: Introducing Camila Ramón, Peloton’s newest cycling instructor. Camila is teaching in both Spanish and English, and she’s bringing a whole new energy and positivity to Peloton. You’ll hear it right away with her music choices, and you’ll see it right away with her dance moves. Camila instills positive, powerful perspectives and approaches to life and relationships with fitness, so you’ll never feel more confident than when you ride with her.
instructors.background: I was born in Argentina and grew up in Miami. Family is everything to me. I’m deeply connected to my community, and I bring that energy with me to every class, every day. Come ride with me!
ordered_q_and_as: How do you motivate?

I motivate through passion and positivity. I care about every person in my class. I teach you to push boundaries. I want you to discover your strength, and after class, I want you to feel like you can take on anything!
Outside of Peloton
Being outdoors centers me. I love hiking, running and camping with my husband and my pup Rex. I love spending time with my vibrant family and eating dulce de leche while binge-watching netflix.
instructors.quote: Juntos en esta comunidad somos imparables.
instructors.name: Camila Ramón

instructors.bio: Leanne is a former professional dancer turned fitness enthusiast who is passionate about movement and self-expression. Leanne has danced since the age of 3, and has worked her way on stage with some of the best-known artists in the world like Taylor Swift, Kylie Minogue and Katy Perry. Leanne’s style of teaching motivates you to step up, and step outside of your comfort zone. She believes that growth comes from areas of discomfort, and through her guidance and support, she’ll get you to the finish line with a smile on your face. Leanne is based in the UK and teaches live from our London studio.
instructors.background: I have been dancing since a very young age, so expressing myself unapologetically through music and movement is second nature. I can’t wait to channel this energy and connect with you in this way on the Bike.
ordered_q_and_as: How Do You Motivate?
I believe that music is what drives us, so I plan to curate meaningful playlists that will push and uplift you. I want you to feel supported but pushed so you get the most out of your time with me.
Outside of Peloton

I love seeing new parts of the world, attending music festivals and rounding out my training through yoga and boxing. I’m always looking for a good piece of pizza or a green juice. Life’s all about balance!
instructors.name: Leanne Hainsby

instructors.bio: Peloton’s VP of Fitness Programming, Robin believes that sweat transforms lives. Her journey to Peloton came after she literally ran herself out of a successful law career. Robin is passionate about guiding Members past their limitations and excuses with inspiring, authentic anecdotes. Author of the New York Times bestseller Shut Up and Run, Robin is a RRCA-certified running coach and ultramarathoner. Her life’s mission is to redefine and rethink possibility through movement.
instructors.music_bio: Ready to ride? Check out a sample of Robin's current class playlist.
instructors.background: A life lived in sweat is my mission. Every day, I work hard planting seeds for tomorrow’s greatness. The hustle in me honors the hustle in you.
ordered_q_and_as: How Do You Motivate?
With a heavy dose of tough love because iron sharpens iron. The pride of hard work lasts longer than the discomfort. And no matter what, just keep showing up.
Outside of Peloton
Always searching for the next best sweat, you can catch me adding up miles and increasing reps around New York City and beyond.
instructors.name: Robin Arzón

instructors.bio: Kirsten welcomes runners of all levels in her motivating classes. A successful career woman turned fitness instructor, Kirsten wholeheartedly embraces the changes that life brings. After seven years of working with the NFL, she shifted her focus to family. Her journey to motherhood was not easy, and fitness helped Kirsten strengthen her body and soul during difficult times. She is now the proud mother of two beautiful daughters and uses her life experiences to fuel her deeply inspiring workouts. Get lifted with Kirsten as you run together to the beats of her favorite hip hop and R&B tracks.
instructors.background: My goal in every class is to remind you that you are more than enough. If it is on your heart to do it, that means you have already been called to it. You just have to take that step, and I’ll be here right alongside you.
ordered_q_and_as: How do you motivate?

Come as you! I coach from a place of learning from past experiences. We get comfortable in the uncomfortable. Let go of the idea of perfection and embrace your uniqueness.That is your superpower! You are a warrior.
Outside of Peloton?

You can find me being a silly mom with my two daughters. Currently, singing and dance parties are our thing. When the babies are asleep, I’m at the gym or listening to the most ratchet music I can find.
instructors.quote: “Don’t let anyone dim your light. You were born to shine, baby!”
instructors.name: Kirsten Ferguson

instructors.bio: Andy takes a technique-centered approach to fitness, drawing on his experience as an accomplished former gymnast and pole vaulter in his home state of Connecticut. A celebrated personal trainer in NYC before joining Peloton, Andy is inspired by the world-class fitness and strength coaches who taught him, and brings his breadth of training knowledge to every workout.
instructors.background: My inspiration for teaching is rooted in helping others improve their lives through fitness, as other coaches have done for me, now it’s my turn to pay it forward.
ordered_q_and_as: How Do You Motivate?
I want members to approach my class with an intent to be challenged and grow. I focus on technique and ensure that there is a purpose behind everything I ask of you.
Outside of Peloton
My training also includes gymnastics, kettlebells, Olympic weightlifting, Muay Thai kickboxing, and yoga. I also enjoy watching documentaries, meditation, reading, and listening to Podcasts.
instructors.name: Andy Speer

instructors.bio: Rebecca’s background in dance, gymnastics and track & field laid a foundation for movement and body awareness that she brings to every Tread class. As a former bootcamp instructor, a Nike master trainer and much more, Rebecca aims to make every workout the best part of the day by celebrating movement and empowering through positivity.
instructors.background: Celebrating movement is the most liberating and charitable thing we can do for ourselves. My goal is to create a moment in everyone’s day that excites them to get moving and enjoy the body they are living in.
ordered_q_and_as: How Do You Motivate?
Movement is power. I’m here to empower you to do your best, every day. Challenges are not roadblocks, they’re reminders that we are stronger and more capable than we imagined, so rise up!
Outside of Peloton

I love to cook and travel! Adventure is in my blood. I love diving into culture by meeting new people, trying local food, recreating recipes from afar, conquering my fears, catching sunsets, and climbing mountains.
instructors.name: Rebecca Kennedy

instructors.bio: A lifelong athlete, Joslyn finds confidence in fitness and running that no one can take away. She believes exercise should be accessible for everyone and has built her career around coaching others to find the confidence to pursue their own goals and cherish their unique bodies—wherever they are on their fitness journey. A powerhouse and a self-proclaimed recovery fiend, she takes a holistic approach to training that nurtures the whole self, because her focus is firmly on the long game. Her warmth, expertise and mantra of “let’s just see” will inspire you to prove to yourself that you can do anything you set your mind to, as long as you’re willing to give it a go.
instructors.short_bio: Joslyn’s classes are spaces where everyone is free to move without judgment, whether it’s their first workout or their thousandth. She encourages you to show up as your full self and discover the power to be your own change.
instructors.background: I want everyone to know that they count, they matter. My classes are a space where you can show up as your full self and discover the power you have to be your own change.
ordered_q_and_as: How Do You Motivate?

I believe fitness is for everyone. Wherever we are on our journeys, we have these incredible bodies that can do so much right now. I want Members to realise this, whether it’s their first class or their thousandth.
Outside of Peloton
My time outside of Peloton is spent hanging with my 3 kings—my husband BJ and my two sons, Bjorn and Max. There’s nowhere I’d rather be!
instructors.quote: Let’s just see how far we can take this
instructors.name: Joslyn Thompson Rule
